Title: What happens inside Postgres when IOPS runs out
Description: In the previous post I wrote about the three cache layers between a SELECT and disk. That post came from a production incident — queries hanging for 35+ minutes, Heroku timeouts, IOPS pinned at 3000. We fixed it. The root cause was bad indexes forcing Postgres to fetch tens of thousands of rows from disk only to discard them. Better indexes, problem solved.
